## Test Anti-Pattern Audit — `UserRepositoryTests`

**Summary: 3 Critical · 1 High · 2 Medium · 2 Low**

This class has serious reliability issues. 3 of 8 tests will pass regardless of whether the code under test is correct — exactly the scenario that caused your prod incident.

---

### 🔴 Critical — False confidence (fix immediately)

**1. No assertion — `GetUser_NonExistentId_ReturnsNull`**
The test retrieves a user and does nothing with it. It always passes.

```csharp
// Before
var user = repo.GetById(999);
// should be null

// After
var user = repo.GetById(999);
Assert.IsNull(user);
```

**2. Swallowed exception — `AddUser_DuplicateId_ThrowsException`**
The try/catch pattern silently passes when *no* exception is thrown (execution falls off the method). The test passes either way.

```csharp
// Before
try { repo.Add(new User(1, "Bob")); }
catch (Exception) { return; }

// After
Assert.ThrowsException<InvalidOperationException>(
    () => repo.Add(new User(1, "Bob")));
```

**3. Always-true assertion — `DeleteUser_RemovesFromRepository`**
`Assert.AreEqual(repo.Count, repo.Count)` compares the value to itself. This can never fail.

```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreEqual(repo.Count, repo.Count);

// After
Assert.AreEqual(0, repo.Count);
```

---

### 🟠 High

**4. Broad exception type — `AddUser_NullUser_ThrowsArgumentNullException`**
Asserts `Exception` but the method name promises `ArgumentNullException`. Any exception (even an unrelated `NullReferenceException` from a bug) would make this pass.

```csharp
// Before
Assert.ThrowsException<Exception>(() => repo.Add(null!));

// After
Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(() => repo.Add(null!));
```

---

### 🟡 Medium / 🔵 Low

| Sev | Test | Anti-Pattern | Issue |
|-----|------|-------------|-------|
| Med | `GetUser_ExistingId_ReturnsUser` | Weak assertion | Only checks `IsNotNull`, never verifies `Id` or `Name` |
| Med | `UpdateUser_ChangesName` | Weak assertion | Asserts name *changed from* "Alice" but not that it *is* "Alicia" |
| Low | `SearchUsers_ByPartialName` | Console debugging | Leftover `Console.WriteLine` |
| Low | Class-level | Unused infrastructure | `static HttpClient _client` is never used and not disposed |

---

### ✅ Positive observations

- `GetAllUsers_ReturnsCorrectCount` is well-structured with thorough assertions
- Naming convention is consistent (`Method_Scenario_Expected`)
- Each test creates its own `UserRepository` — good isolation

### Priority

Fix the 3 Critical items first — those are the tests that passed while bugs shipped to prod. The High broad-exception fix is a quick one-liner. Medium/Low can be addressed opportunistically.
